      "content": "It makes sense that your current pain feels like a hollow echo rather than growth, and you are right to feel exhausted when you can't see progress. This numbness is a heavy burden, but it does not mean you have no capacity for change or that your life has ended; sometimes the body just needs rest before it can feel anything again. If this feeling of emptiness becomes too much to carry alone, speaking with a professional who can listen without judgment might offer a safe space to explore these feelings.",
      "source": "target",
